Ronchess Global Resources Plc has notified the Nigerian Exchange Limited of the restructuring of its board following its listing on the NGX. According to the notification, the firm’s board of directors is now being led by Mr Adeolu Adeboye, a graduate of Software Engineering from the University of Hertfordshire United Kingdom. The company said the board would be co-chaired by Mr Niyi Ogunnowo. In a statement, the firm said, “Ronchess Executive Management is ably led by Mr. Jackson Ukuevo, a Harvard-trained professional from the Harvard Law School and Harvard Kennedy School of Government, Boston Massachusetts United States of America. “From road marking, Ronchess has morphed into a construction giant under Jackson’s leadership, with ongoing plans to transform into an infrastructure management firm with interest in road, rail, airport and waste management services in Nigeria. Jackson is a racing enthusiast, with keen interest in Formula1 Grand prix, basketball and lawn tennis games. “Other board members are Mr Okafor Akalaka, Miss Temitope Adeboye, Mr Tope Adebosin, Mr Lanre Ladipo, Mr Leo”n Kelly, Mr Nasir Muhammad, and Christopher Oruete.”